  "prompt": "How much do psychologists charge for a cognitive behavioural therapy?",
  "response": "The cost of cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT) can vary widely depending on several factors, including the therapist's qualifications, location, and whether the session is in-person or online. On average, here are some general ranges:\n\n- **United States**: Most therapists charge between $100 and $250 per session. Some may charge more, especially in urban areas or if they have specialized training.\n  \n- **United Kingdom**: The cost typically ranges from \u00a340 to \u00a3120 per session, depending on the therapist's experience and location.\n\n- **Canada**: Prices can range from CAD $100 to $200 per session.\n\n- **Australia**: Sessions usually cost between AUD $100 and $250.\n\nIt's also important to check if your insurance covers therapy, as this can significantly reduce out-of-pocket costs. Some therapists may offer sliding scale fees based on income or pro bono services for those who qualify. Online therapy platforms may offer lower rates as well. Always confirm the costs with the therapist beforehand.",
